CNCP v1 22692
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6272: content for literal <template> elements is not readable.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:59.095554+00:00",
  "text": "content for literal <template> elements is not readable.\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.2.37\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codepen.io/leaverou/pen/abYByOO?editors=1010\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nVisit testcase.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nBoth custom elements should render identically\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nThe custom element inside the Vue app renders an empty iframe, because the `<template>` element's content is being emptied by Vue.\r\n~Template elements inside the app but *not* inside a custom element do retain their contents.~\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
